{
    "question_text": "<h3>277. Find the Celebrity</h3><p>Suppose you are at a party with <code>n</code> people (labeled from <code>0</code> to <code>n - 1</code>) and among them, there may exist one celebrity. The definition of a celebrity is that all the other <code>n - 1</code> people know him/her but he/she does not know any of them.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong class=\"example\">Example 1:</strong></p><pre><strong>Input:</strong> graph = [[1,1,0],[0,1,0],[1,1,1]]\n<strong>Output:</strong> 1</pre><p><strong class=\"example\">Example 2:</strong></p><pre><strong>Input:</strong> graph = [[1,0,1],[1,1,0],[0,1,1]]\n<strong>Output:</strong> -1</pre><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Constraints:</strong></p><ul><li><code>2 &lt;= n &lt;= 100</code></li></ul>",
    "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
    "marks": 10,
    "input_format": "n.",
    "output_format": "celebrity id or -1.",
    "constraints": [
        "n <= 100"
    ],
    "explanation": "Two passes: first find a potential candidate (if $A$ knows $B$, $A$ is not celebrity and $B$ might be). Second pass verifies the candidate.",
    "answer": "def findCelebrity(n):\n    cand = 0\n    for i in range(1, n):\n        if knows(cand, i): cand = i\n    for i in range(n):\n        if i != cand and (knows(cand, i) or not knows(i, cand)): return -1\n    return cand",
